cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with image visual try-on, which involves computer vision and graphics techniques to transfer clothing images onto a reference person. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves generating and preserving image content, which falls under the scope of cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves predicting semantic layouts and inpainting, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
